https://www.wikihow.com/Reset-a-Genie-Garage-Door-Opener";s:6:"domain";s:15:"www.wikihow.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:64:{i:0;s:89:"If the garage door wont open or close begin with these garage door troubleshooting steps.";i:1;s:90:"Make sure the opener is plugged in and the garage circuit breaker is in the correct place.";i:2;s:60:"Make sure your door has not been manually locked by mistake.";i:3;s:54:"Replace the batteries of the keypad or remote control.";i:4;s:48:"Why did my garage door wall button stop working.";i:5;s:44:"Garage door remote opens but wont shut door.";i:6;s:118:"I have a 10 year old Craftsman garage door opener model 123953675SRT2 with a wall opener keypad remote and car remote.";i:7;s:57:"The door will always open and close with the wall opener.";i:8;s:75:"In the morning when I am leaving in the car the door will open with any of.";i:9;s:211:"If you decide to use a different remote control button than originally programmed into the opener you need to erase all the learned codes and reprogram each remote control used to operate the garage door opener.";i:10;s:21:"To erase all codes 1.";i:11;s:111:"Press and hold the SRT button on the overhead opener panel until the indicator light turns off about 6 seconds.";i:12;s:97:"If your keypad is closing your garage but not opening it have your partner stand near the keypad.";i:13;s:105:"Set the ladder up near your garage door motor and carefully climb up to the point where you can reach it.";i:14;s:125:"After pressing the learn button on the side of the motor your partner will have 30 seconds to enter the code into the keypad.";i:15;s:84:"Recently my garage door openers keypad stopped opening the garage when code is used.";i:16;s:64:"It does however successfully close the door when key is entered.";i:17;s:77:"The car remote and internal garage remote both work when opening and closing.";i:18;s:106:"New battery has been put into keypad as well as being reprogrammed from chamberlain learn button on motor.";i:19;s:51:"The remotes will not work to close the garage door.";i:20;s:22:"They can only open it.";i:21;s:114:"When this happens your garage door will only close by holding down on the wall button until the door fully closes.";i:22;s:78:"This method is the only way to override the safety sensors and close the door.";i:23;s:50:"All you need to do is reprogram the remote keypad.";i:24;s:40:"On the motor unit find the learn button.";i:25;s:81:"You will have 30 seconds to enter the 4 digit code you want to use on the keypad.";i:26;s:86:"We had a humdinger of a thunder storm today and hear a lightening strike pretty close.";i:27;s:119:"Now the garage door doesnt ooen and close from the inside controller or the keypad from the alarm keypads in the house.";i:28;s:52:"It will only open and close from the outside keypad.";i:29;s:70:"This is because the keypad or remote may miscommunicate with the door.";i:30;s:71:"Likewise when the keypad is out of sync you may need to reset the code.";i:31;s:101:"Luckily if one of these is the culprit you dont have to worry about replacing the entire garage door.";i:32;s:30:"Needs for Professional Repair.";i:33;s:56:"A quick fix wont always cut it and over time our garage.";i:34;s:66:"Some keyless entry keypads have a feature called one button close.";i:35;s:148:"Your garage door opener can be closed by pressing only the ENTER button on the wireless keypad when the one button close feature has been activated.";i:36;s:68:"For security reasons this does not work in reverse to open the door.";i:37;s:184:"Remote controls only work close to the garage door opener Garage Door Opener Losing Range There are many reasons that your remote control will only work when it is close to the opener.";i:38;s:51:"Below is a list of some issues that may cause this.";i:39;s:111:"VisorBattery Antenna LED light bulbs Metal building Issues with the wires to the control panel RF Interference.";i:40;s:92:"This problem occurs when your neighbors garage door operates on the same frequency as yours.";i:41;s:107:"Therefore when they press the remote button to open or close their door they are opening your door as well.";i:42;s:84:"The possible solution is to talk to your neighbors to see whats the actual problems.";i:43;s:56:"You can also reset the code on the clicker of your side.";i:44;s:172:"If the door only closes partway or doesnt respond to the remote it can be frustrating to deal with it when you dont know what the problem is or what you should do about it.";i:45;s:77:"In this guide to garage door opener troubleshooting well discuss a number of.";i:46;s:108:"One of the most common reasons that the garage door may not close is because the lock-out button is engaged.";i:47;s:86:"This button is to prevent the door from opening or closing using the hand-held remote.";i:48;s:82:"To determine if this is the issue press the garage door button on the garage wall.";i:49;s:94:"The problem could be a defect in the remotes or a degradation of the receiver circuit or both.";i:50;s:17:"Heres what to do.";i:51;s:52:"First make sure that the remote batteries are fresh.";i:52;s:70:"Use a battery tester not just a voltmeter or just replace the battery.";i:53;s:103:"Double check that the receiver antenna wire if any is not mangled and has a good connection internally.";i:54;s:112:"I just paid 50 to find out that Liftmaster garage door openers have issues if you place LED bulbs in the opener.";i:55;s:69:"After the tech swapped the bulbs for incandescent it is working fine.";i:56;s:57:"Also 1 sensor is green and 1 is amber and that is normal.";i:57;s:74:"Only adjust the green sensor if you have issues closing without override-.";i:58;s:153:"LiftMaster 877MAX Garage Door Keypad 2290 Completely wireless keypad design holds four unique PIN codes so you can control up to two Garage Door Openers.";i:59;s:124:"Weatherproof slide-up protective cover and backlit numbers on the keypad make it easier than ever to close your garage door.";i:60;s:291:"The technology in the garage door keypad isnt the most sophisticated technology out there as it simply validates the PIN you put in and send a signal to the opener to either open or close the door but yet if it doesnt succeed due to one of the above mentioned reasons it simply wont do that.";i:61;s:96:"To manually open most garage doors you simply pull a corded handle that is attached to the door.";i:62;s:88:"This disengages the electric drive from the door and you can manually open and close it.";i:63;s:64:"To reset it begin by pulling the cord in the opposite direction.";}}